how dangerous River Tam is.

723
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:44,830
She is a mite unpredictable.

724
00:51:45,102 --> 00:51:47,002
Mood swings, of a sort.

725
00:51:47,070 --> 00:51:49,595
It's worse than you know.
It usually is.

726
00:51:49,673 --> 00:51:53,302
That girl will
rain destruction down
on you and your ship.

727
00:51:54,711 --> 00:51:57,475
She is an albatross, Captain.

728
00:51:57,647 --> 00:51:59,376
Way I remember it...

729
00:51:59,483 --> 00:52:02,816
albatross was
a ship's good luck,
till some idiot killed it.

730
00:52:03,353 --> 00:52:06,049
Yes, I've read a poem.
Try not to faint.

731
00:52:06,590 --> 00:52:08,421
I've seen your war record.

732
00:52:09,392 --> 00:52:11,952
I know how you must feel about
the Alliance.

733
00:52:12,229 --> 00:52:14,424
You really don't.
Fair to say.

734
00:52:15,165 --> 00:52:17,998
But I have to hope
you understand,
you can't beat us.

735
00:52:18,068 --> 00:52:19,797
I got no need to beat you.

736
00:52:19,870 --> 00:52:22,737
I just want to go my way.
And you can do that...

737
00:52:23,573 --> 00:52:26,599
once you let me take
River Tam back home.

738
00:52:30,313 --> 00:52:32,838
No, no. You're working
this deal all crabbed.

739
00:52:32,949 --> 00:52:35,645
You got to open with payment.
That is a trap.

740
00:52:35,785 --> 00:52:39,346
I offer money,
you'll play the man of honor
and take umbrage.

741
00:52:39,556 --> 00:52:42,184
I ask you to do what is right,
you'll play the brigand.

742
00:52:42,259 --> 00:52:44,784
I have no stomach for games.

743
00:52:45,295 --> 00:52:47,286
I already know
you will not see reason.

744
00:52:47,364 --> 00:52:48,922
The Alliance wanted to
show me a reason...

745
00:52:48,999 --> 00:52:51,194
they shouldn't have sent
an assassin.

746
00:52:57,440 --> 00:53:00,534
I have a warship
in deep orbit, Captain.

747
00:53:01,211 --> 00:53:04,738
<i>We locked on
to Serenity's pulse beacon
the moment you hit atmo.</i>

748
00:53:04,881 --> 00:53:06,906
I can speak a word
and send a missile...

749
00:53:06,983 --> 00:53:09,679
to that exact location
inside of three minutes.

750
00:53:09,753 --> 00:53:10,913
You do that...

751
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:14,889
you'd best make peace
with your dear
and fluffy lord.

752
00:53:18,662 --> 00:53:19,890
Pulse beacon.

753
00:53:20,163 --> 00:53:24,122
Advice from an old tracker.
You want to find someone,
use your eyes.

754
00:53:24,668 --> 00:53:26,932
How long do you think
you can really run from us?

755
00:53:27,003 --> 00:53:29,631
I never credited
the Alliance with
an overabundance of brains.

756
00:53:29,706 --> 00:53:31,867
And if you're
the best they got...
Captain Reynolds...

757
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:34,740
I should tell you,
so that you don't
waste your time...

758
00:53:34,811 --> 00:53:38,770
you can't make me angry.
Please, spend
an hour with him.

759
00:53:39,549 --> 00:53:42,313
I want to resolve this
like civilized men.

760
00:53:43,386 --> 00:53:45,286
I'm not threatening you.

761
00:53:45,655 --> 00:53:47,122
I'm unarmed.
Good.

762
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:54,288
I am, of course,
wearing full body armor.

763
00:53:54,364 --> 00:53:56,696
I am not a moron.
Wait, just let...

764
00:54:24,894 --> 00:54:26,384
What, no backup?

765
00:54:26,896 --> 00:54:30,093
Making an awful ruckus.
They'll come
when they're needed.

766
00:54:30,166 --> 00:54:31,599
I'd start whistling.

767
00:54:31,735 --> 00:54:34,898
Captain, what do you think
is going to happen here?

768
00:55:21,751 --> 00:55:26,051
Nothing here is what it seems.
He isn't the plucky hero.

769
00:55:26,890 --> 00:55:30,849
The Alliance isn't
some evil empire.
This is not the grand arena.

770
00:55:31,094 --> 00:55:32,721
And that's not incense.

771
00:55:39,736 --> 00:55:40,930
Sir, can you hear me?

772
00:55:41,004 --> 00:55:43,529
Just a flash bomb. Go. Go!

773
00:55:49,245 --> 00:55:52,476
What have you done
to my shuttle?
It's not your shuttle.

774
00:55:52,849 --> 00:55:54,714
Head east. Keep her low.

775
00:56:10,567 --> 00:56:12,364
Okay, forget
the pulse beacon.

776
00:56:12,435 --> 00:56:14,596
<i>There must be another way
to track the ship. </i>

777
00:56:14,671 --> 00:56:16,070
Get a read
on the nav. Sat.

778
00:56:16,139 --> 00:56:18,699
It's a registered transport,
you must be able to locate.

779
00:56:18,775 --> 00:56:19,764
<i>Sir?</i>

780
00:56:19,843 --> 00:56:21,708
Yes, have you found
a nav. Sat. Trajectory?

781
00:56:21,778 --> 00:56:24,212
<i>Sir, we found seven. </i>

782
00:56:31,955 --> 00:56:33,684
<i>We've every reason
to be afraid. </i>

783
00:56:34,090 --> 00:56:37,082
Why, 'cause this guy
beat up Mal?
That ain't so hard.

784
00:56:37,160 --> 00:56:39,685
He didn't beat me up.
Nobody said that.

785
00:56:39,763 --> 00:56:41,526
Because he's a believer.

786
00:56:41,765 --> 00:56:46,202
He's intelligent, methodical,
and devout in his belief...

787
00:56:46,269 --> 00:56:48,669
that killing River
is the right thing to do.

788
00:56:48,738 --> 00:56:51,298
So no hope
of a reward, huh?

789
00:56:52,242 --> 00:56:55,678
Did he say anything
about a Miranda?

790
00:56:56,479 --> 00:56:57,537
What is that?

791
00:56:57,614 --> 00:57:00,014
Don't know who or what,
but it's on River's mind.

792
00:57:00,083 --> 00:57:02,074
Conjure it might be the reason
they're after her.

793
00:57:02,152 --> 00:57:05,053
You think maybe it poses
some kind of threat
to the Alliance?

794
00:57:05,121 --> 00:57:06,486
Do we care?

795
00:57:06,890 --> 00:57:08,585
Are we caring about that?

796
00:57:08,658 --> 00:57:11,320
You dumb-ass hogs,
the only people
she's a threat to is...

797
00:57:11,394 --> 00:57:12,884
us on this boat.

798
00:57:12,962 --> 00:57:14,793
Look, we get back
to Haven...

799
00:57:14,864 --> 00:57:15,888
in a few
hours' time.
Oh, yeah.

800
00:57:15,965 --> 00:57:17,262
Hiding under
the Shepherd's skirts...

801
00:57:17,333 --> 00:57:18,357
that's a manful scheme.

802
00:57:18,435 --> 00:57:20,460
You wanna run this ship?
Yes.

803
00:57:21,538 --> 00:57:23,335
Well, you can't.

804
00:57:24,073 --> 00:57:26,268
Do a damn sight
better job than you.

805
00:57:26,376 --> 00:57:28,810
Getting us lashed over
a couple of strays.

806
00:57:29,045 --> 00:57:31,036
No offense, Doc.
I think it's
noble as a grape...

807
00:57:31,114 --> 00:57:32,342
the way you look to River.

808
00:57:32,415 --> 00:57:34,883
But she ain't my sister
and she ain't your crew.

809
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:37,317
Oh, and neither is she
exactly helpless.

810
00:57:37,687 --> 00:57:40,212
So, where's it writ
that we got to lay down
our lives for her?

811
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:41,848
Which is what you've
steered us toward.

812
00:57:41,925 --> 00:57:43,654
I didn't start this.

813
00:57:44,260 --> 00:57:45,818
No, that's right.

814
00:57:46,663 --> 00:57:50,326
Alliance starts the war,
and then you volunteer.

815
00:57:52,268 --> 00:57:53,963
Battle of Serenity, Mal.

816
00:57:54,037 --> 00:57:57,268
Besides Zoe here, how many...
Hey, I'm talking at you.

817
00:58:01,311 --> 00:58:04,337
How many men in your platoon
came out of there alive?

818
00:58:07,584 --> 00:58:09,711
You wanna leave this room.

819
00:58:12,555 --> 00:58:14,284
Damn right, I do.

820
00:58:21,631 --> 00:58:23,656
This isn't
the war, Mal.

821
00:58:24,534 --> 00:58:26,764
You telling me that
'cause you think I don't know?

822
00:58:26,836 --> 00:58:28,963
You came to the Training House
looking for a fight.

823
00:58:29,038 --> 00:58:30,938
I came looking for you.

824
00:58:32,242 --> 00:58:34,710
I just want to know
who I'm dealing with.

825
00:58:34,811 --> 00:58:37,439
I've seen too many versions
of you to be sure.

826
00:58:37,680 --> 00:58:41,946
I start fighting a war,
I guarantee
you'll see something new.

827
00:58:49,125 --> 00:58:50,353
We'll get off.

828
00:58:50,426 --> 00:58:52,053
River and I will
get off at Haven.

829
00:58:52,128 --> 00:58:53,891
We'll find some...
Nobody's saying that.

830
00:58:53,963 --> 00:58:55,794
Nobody besides Jayne
is saying that.

831
00:58:55,865 --> 00:58:56,854
Mal.

832
00:58:59,335 --> 00:59:02,429
I got no answers
for you, Inara.
I got no rudder.

833
00:59:02,505 --> 00:59:05,474
Wind blows northerly,
I go north.
That's who I am.

834
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:08,102
Now, maybe that ain't
a man to lead,
but they have to follow.

835
00:59:08,177 --> 00:59:09,269
So you wanna tear me down...

836
00:59:09,345 --> 00:59:11,506
do it inside your own mind.
I'm not trying
to tear you down.

837
00:59:11,581 --> 00:59:13,173
But you fog things up.

838
00:59:13,983 --> 00:59:15,678
You always have.

839
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:18,753
You spin me about.

840
00:59:21,958 --> 00:59:24,119
I wish like hell
you was elsewhere.

841
00:59:26,329 --> 00:59:27,421
I was.

842
01:01:00,556 --> 01:01:02,820
No trouble,
little crazy person.

843
01:01:04,827 --> 01:01:08,194
We're going
for a nice shuttle ride.

844
01:01:25,715 --> 01:01:27,512
She's out. Jayne's down.

845
01:01:27,717 --> 01:01:30,242
The other way.
Find her and do not engage.

846
01:01:52,686 --> 01:01:54,176
It's gonna be okay...

847
01:02:04,765 --> 01:02:06,926
She's sealed off the bridge.
I do not like her there.

848
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:08,695
Check the shuttle.
She could have snuck in.

849
01:02:08,769 --> 01:02:09,758
Captain.

850
01:02:55,816 --> 01:02:58,717
The government's man,
he says you're a danger to us.

851
01:02:59,719 --> 01:03:01,346
Not worth helping.

852
01:03:03,957 --> 01:03:05,117
Is he right?

853
01:03:06,459 --> 01:03:08,859
Are you anything but a weapon?

854
01:03:12,032 --> 01:03:15,126
I've staked my crew's life on
the theory you're a person...

855
01:03:15,202 --> 01:03:18,399
actual and whole,
and if I'm wrong,
you'd best shoot me now.

856
01:03:19,639 --> 01:03:21,504
Or we could talk more.

857
01:03:32,552 --> 01:03:33,644
Miranda.

858
01:03:37,757 --> 01:03:40,157
How can it be there's
a whole planet
called Miranda...

859
01:03:40,227 --> 01:03:41,489
and none of us knowed that?

860
01:03:41,561 --> 01:03:44,928
Because there isn't one.
It's a blackrock.
Uninhabitable.

861
01:03:45,432 --> 01:03:48,492
Terraforming didn't hold,
or some such.
Few settlers died.

862
01:03:48,568 --> 01:03:50,092
Was it right before the war?

863
01:03:50,170 --> 01:03:54,038
I had to show them.
I didn't know if you were
going to make me sleep.

864
01:03:55,742 --> 01:03:57,835
You could have asked.
Wait a tick, yeah.

865
01:03:57,911 --> 01:04:01,574
Some years back,
there was call for workers
to settle on Miranda.

866
01:04:01,648 --> 01:04:03,411
Daddy talked about it.
Nothing about it...

867
01:04:03,483 --> 01:04:05,508
on the Cortex.
History, Astronomy,
it's not in there.

868
01:04:05,585 --> 01:04:07,917
Half of writing history
is hiding the truth.

869
01:04:07,988 --> 01:04:10,923
There's something
on that rock the Alliance
doesn't want known.

870
01:04:10,991 --> 01:04:13,186
That's right at the edge
of the Burnham Quadrant,
right?

871
01:04:13,260 --> 01:04:15,592
Furthest planet out?
It's not that far from here.

872
01:04:15,662 --> 01:04:17,391
Whoa. No. No. Honey...
That's a bad notion.

873
01:04:17,464 --> 01:04:19,830
...you show them the bad.
I got it, baby.

874
01:04:23,470 --> 01:04:26,132
This is us, at Haven,
and here's Miranda.

875
01:04:26,706 --> 01:04:30,904
All along here,
that empty space in between,
that's Reaver territory.

876
01:04:30,977 --> 01:04:33,673
They just float out there,
sending out raiding parties.

877
01:04:33,747 --> 01:04:36,045
Nobody ventures there.
Not even the Alliance.

878
01:04:36,116 --> 01:04:38,380
You go through that,
you're signing up
to be a banquet.

879
01:04:38,451 --> 01:04:41,079
I'm on board with our standard
run-and-hide scenario.

880
01:04:41,154 --> 01:04:42,883
And we are just about...

881
01:04:43,657 --> 01:04:44,646
Wait.

882
01:05:02,042 --> 01:05:04,169
Doesn't look like Reavers.
Wasn't.

883
01:05:10,016 --> 01:05:11,005
Shepherd?

884
01:05:12,819 --> 01:05:13,945
Shepherd?

885
01:05:15,288 --> 01:05:16,550
Shepherd Book?

886
01:05:37,610 --> 01:05:39,043
Get the Doc.

887
01:05:40,480 --> 01:05:41,469
Shepherd.

888
01:05:42,649 --> 01:05:45,516
Don't move.
Won't go far.

889
01:05:48,021 --> 01:05:50,012
Shouldn't have been you.

890
01:05:50,824 --> 01:05:53,452
Alliance should've hit us.
Should've hit me.

891
01:05:54,828 --> 01:05:56,557
That crossed my mind.

892
01:06:01,101 --> 01:06:04,229
I shot him down.
Yeah. I see.

893
01:06:04,471 --> 01:06:07,031
I killed the ship
that killed us.

894
01:06:08,775 --> 01:06:10,743
Not very Christian of me.

895
01:06:11,211 --> 01:06:12,735
You did what's right.

896
01:06:13,213 --> 01:06:17,274
Coming from you,
that means almost nothing.

897
01:06:22,856 --> 01:06:25,416
I'm long gone.
No, Doc will bring
you around.

898
01:06:25,492 --> 01:06:28,393
I look to be bored
by many more sermons
before you slip.

899
01:06:28,461 --> 01:06:29,723
Just don't move.

900
01:06:30,363 --> 01:06:32,160
Can't order me
around, boy.

901
01:06:33,433 --> 01:06:35,196
I'm not one
of your crew.

902
01:06:37,303 --> 01:06:38,702
Yes, you are.

903
01:06:41,541 --> 01:06:43,406
River...
Come on.

904
01:06:43,843 --> 01:06:44,832
Hey.

905
01:06:46,613 --> 01:06:50,572
I don't care
what you believe.
Just believe it.

906
01:06:52,252 --> 01:06:54,049
Whatever you...

907
01:07:27,520 --> 01:07:29,545
How come
they ain't waiting?

908
01:07:30,723 --> 01:07:33,692
They knowed we was coming,
how come they only sent one?

909
01:07:34,828 --> 01:07:37,160
They didn't know
we were coming here.

910
01:07:37,964 --> 01:07:39,659
Get on the Cortex.

911
01:07:39,766 --> 01:07:41,631
Wave, Li Shen,
the Sanchez brothers...

912
01:07:41,701 --> 01:07:45,193
anyone who has ever
sheltered us after a heist.
Tell them to get out.

913
01:07:45,271 --> 01:07:46,499
Get out now.

914
01:07:57,684 --> 01:07:58,844
<i>I'm sorry. </i>

915
01:08:00,987 --> 01:08:04,753
<i>If your quarry goes to ground,
leave no ground to go to. </i>

916
01:08:05,892 --> 01:08:07,917
<i>You should have
taken my offer. </i>

917
01:08:07,994 --> 01:08:10,554
<i>Or did you think none of this
was your fault?</i>

918
01:08:10,830 --> 01:08:12,798
I don't murder children.

919
01:08:13,199 --> 01:08:14,188
<i>I do. </i>

920
01:08:15,135 --> 01:08:17,160
<i>If I have to.
Why?</i>

921
01:08:19,038 --> 01:08:21,199
Do you even know
why they sent you?

922
01:08:21,975 --> 01:08:23,738
<i>It's not my place to ask. </i>

923
01:08:24,978 --> 01:08:27,503
<i>I believe in something
greater than myself. </i>

924
01:08:28,615 --> 01:08:30,014
<i>A better world. </i>

925
01:08:30,650 --> 01:08:32,481
<i>A world without sin. </i>

926
01:08:33,019 --> 01:08:35,010
So me and mine
gotta lay down and die...

927
01:08:35,088 --> 01:08:37,283
so you can live
in your better world?

928
01:08:37,757 --> 01:08:39,884
<i>I'm not going to live there. </i>

929
01:08:40,293 --> 01:08:41,885
<i>There's no place
for me there... </i>

930
01:08:41,961 --> 01:08:44,429
<i>any more than
there is for you. Malcolm... </i>

931
01:08:44,597 --> 01:08:45,859
<i>I'm a monster. </i>

932
01:08:47,534 --> 01:08:48,831
<i>What I do is evil. </i>

933
01:08:48,902 --> 01:08:51,462
<i>I have no illusions about it,
but it must be done. </i>

934
01:08:51,538 --> 01:08:53,005
Keep talking.

935
01:08:53,306 --> 01:08:55,365
You're not getting
a location trace
off this wave.

936
01:08:55,441 --> 01:08:59,343
<i>And every minute
you keep River Tam from me,
more people will die. </i>

937
01:08:59,412 --> 01:09:01,903
<i>You think I care?
Of course you care. </i>

938
01:09:02,882 --> 01:09:04,611
<i>You're not a Reaver, Mal. </i>

939
01:09:05,118 --> 01:09:08,576
<i>You're a human man
and you will never
understand how... </i>

940
01:09:14,861 --> 01:09:16,658
Get these bodies together.

941
01:09:17,197 --> 01:09:18,494
We got time
for grave digging?

942
01:09:18,565 --> 01:09:20,055
Zoe, you and Simon
rope them together.

943
01:09:20,133 --> 01:09:22,499
Five or six.
I want them laid out
on the nose of our ship.

944
01:09:22,569 --> 01:09:23,695
Are you insane?

945
01:09:23,770 --> 01:09:25,067
I won't desecrate
these bodies.

946
01:09:25,138 --> 01:09:27,003
I don't understand.
What do you mean,
the bodies...

947
01:09:27,073 --> 01:09:28,506
I want you to muck up
the reactor core.

948
01:09:28,575 --> 01:09:30,600
Just enough to leave a trail
and make it read like...

949
01:09:30,677 --> 01:09:32,838
we're flying
without containment,
not enough to fry us.

950
01:09:32,912 --> 01:09:34,709
These people
are our friends.
Kaylee...

951
01:09:34,781 --> 01:09:37,614
you got a day's work to do
and two hours to do it.

952
01:09:38,651 --> 01:09:42,917
Jayne, you and Wash
hoist up the cannon mount.
Goes right on top.

953
01:09:42,989 --> 01:09:44,650
Piece or two
of the other ship,
stick it on.

954
01:09:44,724 --> 01:09:47,955
Any place you can tear hull
without inner breach,
do that, too.

955
01:09:48,795 --> 01:09:52,060
We're gonna need paint.
We're gonna need red paint.

956
01:09:52,565 --> 01:09:53,554
Sir...

957
01:09:54,033 --> 01:09:57,491
do you really mean
to turn our home
into an abomination...

