1198
01:36:34,999 --> 01:36:36,489
Zoe, gorrammit!

1199
01:36:52,383 --> 01:36:54,715
Zoe, get your ass
back on the line!

1200
01:37:11,202 --> 01:37:12,897
You shot me in the back!

1201
01:37:14,572 --> 01:37:17,006
I haven't made you
angry, have I?

1202
01:37:17,075 --> 01:37:20,238
There are a lot
of innocent people in the air
being killed right now.

1203
01:37:20,311 --> 01:37:22,745
You have no idea
how true that is.

1204
01:37:24,182 --> 01:37:25,843
I know the secret.

1205
01:37:26,618 --> 01:37:29,086
The truth that burned up
River Tam's brain.

1206
01:37:29,854 --> 01:37:33,915
Rest of the 'verse
is going to know it, too.
'Cause they need to.

1207
01:37:35,860 --> 01:37:39,193
Do you really believe that?
I do.

1208
01:37:39,597 --> 01:37:41,724
You willing to die
for that belief?

1209
01:37:44,135 --> 01:37:45,329
I am.

1210
01:37:52,110 --> 01:37:54,169
Of course,
that ain't exactly Plan A.

1211
01:38:20,805 --> 01:38:22,932
Spine's intact.
Just give me a bandage.

1212
01:39:16,594 --> 01:39:18,027
Up high, left!

1213
01:39:25,770 --> 01:39:27,203
Kaylee!

1214
01:39:39,851 --> 01:39:43,787
Fall back! Everybody,
fall back! Fall back now!

1215
01:39:53,398 --> 01:39:54,695
Jayne, grenade.

1216
01:39:56,034 --> 01:39:58,229
Very last one.

1217
01:40:04,275 --> 01:40:05,367
They're gonna get in.

1218
01:40:05,710 --> 01:40:08,406
I can close it
from the outside.

1219
01:40:08,813 --> 01:40:10,804
No one's coming
back from that.

1220
01:40:13,818 --> 01:40:15,752
How much ammo
do we have?

1221
01:40:15,853 --> 01:40:19,755
Three, four max,
and my swinging cod.
That's all.

1222
01:40:19,824 --> 01:40:20,848
The lift isn't moving.

1223
01:40:20,925 --> 01:40:23,393
When they come,
try to plug
the hole with it.

1224
01:40:23,461 --> 01:40:25,895
I'm starting to lose
some feeling here.

1225
01:40:25,963 --> 01:40:28,659
Lie still. I'm going
to give you something...

1226
01:40:30,701 --> 01:40:31,690
My bag.

1227
01:40:42,013 --> 01:40:43,537
Keep pressure here.

1228
01:40:45,316 --> 01:40:46,305
My bag.

1229
01:40:46,851 --> 01:40:47,840
I need...

1230
01:40:48,686 --> 01:40:52,144
adrenaline and a shot of...

1231
01:40:52,657 --> 01:40:54,249
calaphar for Kaylee.

1232
01:40:56,961 --> 01:40:58,656
I can't.

1233
01:41:02,533 --> 01:41:03,522
River.

1234
01:41:08,606 --> 01:41:11,302
River, I'm sorry.
No.

1235
01:41:12,677 --> 01:41:13,803
No.

1236
01:41:20,985 --> 01:41:23,215
I hate to leave.
You won't.

1237
01:41:26,157 --> 01:41:28,751
You take care of me, Simon.

1238
01:41:31,829 --> 01:41:34,457
You've always
taken care of me.

1239
01:41:39,804 --> 01:41:40,930
My turn.

1240
01:42:35,826 --> 01:42:38,454
Do you know
what your sin is, Mal?

1241
01:42:39,030 --> 01:42:42,397
Hell. I'm a fan
of all seven.

1242
01:42:48,940 --> 01:42:50,703
But right now...

1243
01:42:51,776 --> 01:42:53,744
I'm going to have
to go with wrath.

1244
01:42:58,216 --> 01:43:00,684
We ain't got long.

1245
01:43:06,724 --> 01:43:08,589
You suppose he got through?

1246
01:43:09,860 --> 01:43:11,828
Do you think Mal
got the word out?

1247
01:43:12,496 --> 01:43:16,899
He got through.
I know he got through.

1248
01:43:28,179 --> 01:43:29,168
I'm sorry.

1249
01:43:32,483 --> 01:43:35,281
You should know
there's no shame in this.

1250
01:43:37,455 --> 01:43:39,582
You've done remarkable things.

1251
01:43:40,825 --> 01:43:43,020
But you're fighting a war...

1252
01:43:44,228 --> 01:43:45,422
you've already lost.

1253
01:43:50,268 --> 01:43:52,168
Well, I'm known for that.

1254
01:44:01,078 --> 01:44:04,707
Piece of shrapnel tore up
that nerve cluster
my first tour.

1255
01:44:05,283 --> 01:44:06,614
Had it moved.

1256
01:44:08,219 --> 01:44:09,652
Sorry about the throat.

1257
01:44:10,254 --> 01:44:13,087
Expect you'd want to say your
famous last words right now.

1258
01:44:14,158 --> 01:44:15,716
Just one trouble.

1259
01:44:20,464 --> 01:44:21,954
I ain't gonna kill you.

1260
01:44:25,436 --> 01:44:28,530
Hell, I'm gonna grant
your greatest wish.

1261
01:44:35,880 --> 01:44:38,713
I'm gonna show you
a world without sin.

1262
01:44:44,555 --> 01:44:46,614
<i>These are just a few of
the few images we've recorded. </i>

1263
01:44:46,691 --> 01:44:47,680
<i>And you can see... </i>

1264
01:44:50,594 --> 01:44:52,755
<i>it isn't what we thought. </i>

1265
01:44:54,465 --> 01:44:56,330
<i>There's been no war here... </i>

1266
01:44:57,034 --> 01:45:01,300
<i>and no terraforming event.
The environment is stable. </i>

1267
01:45:02,973 --> 01:45:04,736
<i>It's the Pax. </i>

1268
01:45:06,410 --> 01:45:10,744
<i>The G-23 Paxilon Hydroclorate
that we added
to the air processors. </i>

1269
01:45:11,449 --> 01:45:14,043
<i>It was supposed to calm
the population... </i>

1270
01:45:42,646 --> 01:45:44,307
<i>We meant it for the best... </i>

1271
01:45:45,216 --> 01:45:46,774
<i>to make people safer. </i>

1272
01:45:48,552 --> 01:45:49,849
<i>God!</i>

1273
01:46:12,710 --> 01:46:15,178
Sir?
It's done.

1274
01:46:18,349 --> 01:46:19,680
Report.

1275
01:46:21,852 --> 01:46:23,012
River?

1276
01:46:48,579 --> 01:46:49,568
Drop your weapons!

1277
01:46:49,647 --> 01:46:50,671
Do it now.

1278
01:46:50,748 --> 01:46:52,215
Weapons down.
Let it down, now.

1279
01:46:52,283 --> 01:46:53,875
I want to see
your hands in the air.

1280
01:46:53,951 --> 01:46:55,816
Stand down.
Do it.

1281
01:47:01,292 --> 01:47:02,759
Targets are acquired.

1282
01:47:02,827 --> 01:47:04,226
<i>Do we have a kill order?</i>

1283
01:47:07,198 --> 01:47:08,961
<i>Do we have an order?</i>

1284
01:47:17,107 --> 01:47:18,369
<i>Stand down. </i>

1285
01:47:19,510 --> 01:47:22,274
<i>Stand down. It's finished. </i>

1286
01:47:26,050 --> 01:47:27,415
<i>We're finished. </i>

1287
01:49:29,807 --> 01:49:31,672
It's not over,
you know.

1288
01:49:33,377 --> 01:49:36,073
I can't guarantee
that they won't
come after you.

1289
01:49:36,914 --> 01:49:37,903
The Parliament.

1290
01:49:38,782 --> 01:49:41,774
Your broadwave about Miranda
has weakened their regime.

1291
01:49:41,852 --> 01:49:46,221
They are not gone
and they are not... forgiving.

1292
01:49:46,790 --> 01:49:49,258
That don't bode
especially well for you...

1293
01:49:49,994 --> 01:49:53,020
giving the order to let us go,
patching up our hurt.

1294
01:49:54,398 --> 01:49:57,834
I told them the Tams
were no longer a threat,
damage done.

1295
01:49:58,369 --> 01:49:59,893
They might listen...

1296
01:50:00,638 --> 01:50:04,039
but I think they know
I'm no longer their man.

1297
01:50:05,809 --> 01:50:08,903
They take you down,
I don't expect
to grieve over much.

1298
01:50:11,148 --> 01:50:13,582
Like to kill you myself,
I see you again.

1299
01:50:14,418 --> 01:50:15,407
You won't.

1300
01:50:18,355 --> 01:50:20,550
There is nothing left to see.

1301
01:50:26,263 --> 01:50:27,787
Sir, we have
a green light.

1302
01:50:28,198 --> 01:50:30,428
Inspection's pos
and we're clear
for up-thrust.

1303
01:50:36,940 --> 01:50:39,033
Think she'll hold together?

1304
01:50:40,044 --> 01:50:42,672
She's tore up plenty.
But she'll fly true.

1305
01:50:46,984 --> 01:50:49,214
Make sure
everything's secure.

1306
01:50:51,088 --> 01:50:53,989
Could be bumpy.
Always is.

1307
01:51:01,398 --> 01:51:02,422
Taking her out...

1308
01:51:02,499 --> 01:51:05,059
should be about a day's ride
to get you back to your girls.

1309
01:51:05,135 --> 01:51:06,295
Right.

1310
01:51:07,705 --> 01:51:09,935
Ready to get off this heap,
back to civilized life?

1311
01:51:10,007 --> 01:51:10,996
I, uh...

1312
01:51:15,779 --> 01:51:17,144
I don't know.

1313
01:51:19,149 --> 01:51:20,309
Good answer.

1314
01:51:45,542 --> 01:51:48,067
So, you gonna ride
shotgun with me,
help me fly?

1315
01:51:48,312 --> 01:51:49,540
That's the plan.

1316
01:51:50,214 --> 01:51:51,772
Think you can work out...

1317
01:51:59,423 --> 01:52:00,412
Okay.

1318
01:52:01,792 --> 01:52:04,920
Clearly some
aptitude for the...

1319
01:52:06,430 --> 01:52:08,955
It ain't all buttons
and charts, little albatross.

1320
01:52:09,399 --> 01:52:11,526
You know what the first rule
of flying is?

1321
01:52:12,035 --> 01:52:15,027
Well, I suppose you do,
since you already know
what I'm about to say.

1322
01:52:16,073 --> 01:52:17,540
I do.

1323
01:52:18,709 --> 01:52:20,438
But I like to hear you say it.

1324
01:52:25,249 --> 01:52:26,238
Love.

1325
01:52:26,583 --> 01:52:28,483
You can learn all the math
in the 'verse...

1326
01:52:28,552 --> 01:52:30,577
but you take a boat in
the air that you don't love...

1327
01:52:30,654 --> 01:52:33,521
she'll shake you off
just as sure as
the turn of the worlds.

1328
01:52:36,860 --> 01:52:39,556
Love keeps her in the air
when she ought to fall down...

1329
01:52:41,031 --> 01:52:43,363
tells you she's hurting
before she keels.

1330
01:52:46,170 --> 01:52:47,398
Makes her a home.

1331
01:52:52,976 --> 01:52:54,841
Storm's getting worse.

1332
01:52:57,147 --> 01:52:59,843
We'll pass through it
soon enough.

1333
01:53:20,938 --> 01:53:21,870
<i>What was that?</i>

